Warszyn  (formerly German Warsin) is a village in the administrative district of Gmina Dolice, within Stargard County, West Pomeranian Voivodeship, in north-western Poland. It lies approximately  south-east of Stargard and  south-east of the regional capital Szczecin.
For the history of the region, see History of Pomerania.
The village has a population of 300.
